'''Contextual empiricism''' is a [[theory]] about validating scientific knowledge. It is the view that scientific knowledge is shaped by [[contextualism|contextual]] values as well as constitutive ones.<ref>Janet Kourany, ''Scientific Knowledge''</ref> <ref>Thibodeaux, Jarrett. 2014. "Three Versions of Constructionism and their Reliance on Social Conditions in Social Problems Research". ''Sociology''. 48(4): 829-837.</ref>

